{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fighting|type2=Steel}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Lucario}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fighting|prevnum=447|prev=Riolu|nextnum=449|next=Hippopotas|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Lucario}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Lucario\n|jname=ルカリオ\n|jtranslit=Rukario\n|tmname=Lucario\n|forme=2\n|form2=Mega Lucario\n|image2=448Lucario-Mega.png\n|mega=Lucarionite\n|ndex=448\n|sdex=116\n|u2dex=034\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=063\n|adex=280\n|abrow=223\n|obrow=265\n|opbrow=179\n|type1=Fighting\n|type2=Steel\n|category=Aura\n|height-ftin=3\'11"\n|height-m=1.2\n|height-ftin2=4\'03"\n|height-m2=1.3\n|weight-lbs=119.0\n|weight-kg=54.0\n|weight-lbs2=126.8\n|weight-kg2=57.5\n|abilitylayout=2+1\n|abilitycolm=2\n|ability1=Steadfast\n|ability2=Inner Focus\n|abilitym=Adaptability\n|abilityd=Justified\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Field\n|egggroup2=Human-Like\n|eggcycles=25\n|evtotal=2\n|evat=1\n|evsa=1\n|expyield=184\n|oldexp=204\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=31\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=45\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=lucario\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Lucario\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ルカリオ\'\'\' \'\'Lucario\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Fighting|Steel}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Riolu}} when [[level]]ed up with high [[friendship]] during the [[Time|day]]. It can [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolve]] into \'\'\'Mega Lucario\'\'\' using the [[Lucarionite]].\n\n==Biology==\nLucario is a bipedal, canine-like Pokémon, with fur that is predominantly blue and black. It possesses a short, round spike on the back of each forepaw, in addition to a third on its chest. It has red eyes, a long snout and ears. When its mouth is open, two pairs of pointed teeth, one in the upper jaw and one in the lower, can be seen. It possesses cream-colored fur on its torso, and blue fur on its thighs that resembles shorts. It has a medium length tail of the same blue color as well. It stands on its toes rather than on its entire foot. It has developed four black appendages that hang down from its head, which rise when Lucario reads or manipulates [[aura]], a special energy that it senses. Lucario can study this energy to predict the movements of their opponents and track their quarry. They also have the power to manipulate this energy in an offensive manner, in the form of explosive spheres of energy. Lucario can understand human speech, and have been reported to communicate with humans through telepathy.\n\nAs Mega Lucario, its cream fur becomes longer, and its thighs slim down. It develops more spikes on the back of its paws, which have turned crimson. It also develops spikes on both of its feet, which have become crimson too. Its previously red eyes are now orange-colored. Its aura-sensing appendages grow longer, and two of them are tipped in crimson. Its shoulders also possess a spike each. Its aura heightens throughout its body, which formed black markings on its blue fur.<ref>http://www.pokemonxy.com/en-us/pokemon/mega_pokemon/#Lucario</ref> In [[Kalos]], Mega Lucario is believed to be the first discovered Mega Evolution. People call Mega Lucario\'s fighting style heartless due to it being bathed in combative instincts and not showing any mercy to any other opposing Pokémon.\n\nLucario is considered to be prideful, and is extremely loyal to its Trainer. It also seems to have a natural sense of justice. It usually lives deep in mountains very far from people to improve their skills. It is an exceptionally rare Pokémon. Lucario are primarily carnivores, hunting their prey in packs, though {{mov|Lucario|one Lucario|8}} was seen eating Berries and plants, like roses. It has been seen eating chocolate, even though chocolate is not part of its natural diet.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Lucario anime.png|thumb|250px|Lucario in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Lucario (M08)]]=====\nLucario debuted as one of the main Pokémon in \'\'[[M08|Lucario and the Mystery of Mew]]\'\'. He belonged to [[Sir Aaron]] and was sealed away in his staff for a thousand years. Ash later released him during a festival and he helped guide him to the [[Tree of Beginning]] after {{OBP|Mew|M08}} teleported {{AP|Pikachu}} there. However, he sacrificed himself to save the Tree of Beginning.\n\n=====[[Maylene\'s Lucario]]=====\nLucario\'s main series debut was in \'\'[[DP066|Lost Leader Strategy!]]\'\' as [[Maylene]]\'s main Pokémon; it was first seen {{pkmn|battle|battling}} with Maylene in their {{pkmn|training}}. Lucario used {{m|Aura Sphere}} to stop the battle of {{TP|Paul|Electabuzz}}, {{TP|Dawn|Piplup}}, and {{AP|Pikachu}}. It was used in Maylene\'s matches with [[Paul]], {{an|Dawn}}, and {{Ash}}.\n\n=====[[Riley\'s Lucario]]=====\n[[Riley]]\'s Lucario debuted in \'\'[[DP110|Steeling Peace of Mind!]]\'\' at [[Iron Island]]. When {{Ash}} and {{ashfr}} traveled there after being contacted by {{an|Barry}}, they found the local {{type|Steel}} Pokémon fighting brutally against each other and the other Pokémon on the island. When a crazed {{p|Aggron}} attacked Ash, Riley stepped in and had Lucario attack it with {{m|Close Combat}}. Despite being a Steel-type as well, Lucario wasn\'t immediately affected like the others of its type due to its strong [[aura]].\n\n=====[[Cameron\'s Lucario]]=====\n{{un|Cameron}}\'s {{p|Riolu}} evolved into a Lucario in \'\'[[BW107|Cameron\'s Secret Weapon!]]\'\' in a [[Vertress Conference]] battle against [[Ash\'s Snivy]]. It beat Snivy and fought against [[Ash\'s Pikachu]] in \'\'[[BW108|A Unova League Evolution]]\'\', and won, but lost to [[Virgil]]\'s {{DL|Virgil|Flareon}} later in the episode. It tends to [[Walking Pokémon|walk outside of its Poké Ball]].\n\n=====[[Korrina\'s Lucario]]=====\n[[Korrina]]\'s Lucario debuted in \'\'[[XY030|Mega Revelations!]]\'\' as her [[walking Pokémon]]. The duo obtained a [[Lucarionite]] in the [[XY031|following episode]], allowing it to [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolve]]. Korrina later used Lucario in her [[Gym]] {{pkmn|battle}} against Ash, and later during the battle to stop the [[Giant Rock]]. It previously evolved from a Riolu. It was often seen [[Walking Pokémon|outside of its Poké Ball]] in the episodes it appeared in.\n\n[[File:Korrina Mega Lucario.png|thumb|250px|Mega Lucario in the anime]]\n\n=====Other=====\nA Lucario that can Mega Evolve into Mega Lucario appeared in \'\'[[XY032|The Aura Storm!]]\'\', under the ownership of Korrina\'s grandfather [[Gurkinn]]. Gurkinn\'s Lucario was used in a battle against Korrina\'s own Lucario, but when Korrina\'s Lucario lost control when it Mega Evolved, Gurkinn\'s Lucario had to knock it out.\n\nA Lucario appeared in \'\'[[M20|I Choose You!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Sorrel]].\n\nA Lucario appeared in [[SM140]], under the ownership of {{an|Professor Kukui}}. It was sent out to battle a {{Shiny}} {{DL|Ultra Beasts (anime)|Shiny Guzzlord|Guzzlord}} that interrupted the closing ceremony of the [[Manalo Conference]], only to be defeated and recalled to its {{i|Poké Ball}}. Lucario then reappeared in [[SM142]] and [[SM143]], where it was Kukui\'s fifth Pokémon during his [[Full Battle]] against Ash. It went up against [[Ash\'s Naganadel]].\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA Lucario made a cameo appearance in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M10|The Rise of Darkrai]]\'\', where it was seen dodging a {{p|Rayquaza}}\'s {{m|Hyper Beam}}.\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Lucario was seen on [[Television|TV]] in \'\'[[DP150|Unlocking the Red Chain of Events!]]\'\'. It was participating in a [[Double Performance]] alongside a {{p|Froslass}}.\n\nA Lucario that can Mega Evolve into Mega Lucario appeared in the opening of \'\'[[XYS01|Mega Evolution Special I]]\'\'.\n\nA Lucario that can Mega Evolve into Mega Lucario appeared in a flashback or a fantasy in \'\'[[XY043|Origins of Mega Evolution!]]\'\'.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP066|Lucario|Ash\'s Pokédex|Lucario, the Aura Pokémon, and the evolved form of {{p|Riolu}}. By sensing the [[aura]] of its opponents, Lucario can read their thoughts and movements.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW108|Lucario|Cameron\'s Pokédex|Lucario, the Aura Pokémon. Lucario has the power to detect their opponent\'s thoughts and actions by reading their aura.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Black & White\'\'|Unova}}\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY030|Lucario|Ash\'s Pokédex|Lucario, the Aura Pokémon and the evolved form of {{p|Riolu}}. Lucario reads the thoughts of others and anticipates their movements by sensing their auras.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Black 2 and White 2 Animated Trailer===\n[[File:Nate Lucario Aura Sphere Animated Trailer.png|thumb|250px|Lucario in the animated trailer]]\nA Lucario appeared in the [[Pokémon Black Version 2 and Pokémon White Version 2 Animated Trailer]], under the ownership of {{ga|Nate}}. It and its Trainer pursued a member of the [[Shadow Triad]] across the frozen [[Opelucid City]], but despite their efforts to stop him, that member escaped with his comrades.\n{{-}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Masters Animated Trailer===\n[[File:Korrina Lucario Masters Aura Sphere.png|250px|thumb|Korrina\'s Lucario in the [[Pokémon Masters Animated Trailer]]]]\n====[[Korrina\'s Lucario]]====\nKorrina\'s Lucario appeared in the [[Pokémon Masters Animated Trailer]]. Alongside [[Cheren]]\'s {{p|Stoutland}} and [[Misty\'s Starmie]], it battled [[Cynthia\'s Garchomp]], [[Steven\'s Metagross]], and [[Lance\'s Dragonite]]. At the behest of its {{pkmn|Trainer}}, Lucario tried to catch Stoutland after it was knocked back by Garchomp\'s {{m|Dragon Claw}}, but this backfired and both Pokémon were incapacitated. After Starmie defended it and Stoutland from Dragonite\'s {{m|Hyper Beam}}, Lucario defended itself from Metagross\'s {{m|Flash Cannon}} with Aura Sphere.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Korrina Lucario Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Lucario in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n[[File:Korrina Mega Lucario Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Mega Lucario in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the movie adaptations===\n{{main|Lucario (M08)}}\nThe Lucario from the eighth movie appears in [[Lucario and the Mystery of Mew (manga)|the adaptation]].\n\n===In the Phantom Thief Pokémon 7 manga===\n{{main|Hiori\'s Lucario}}\nLucario is [[Hiori]]\'s primary Pokémon in [[Phantom Thief Pokémon 7]].\n\n===In the Pocket Monsters B2 W2 ~ A New Legend ~ manga===\nA Lucario appeared in [[ANL5]], under the ownership of [[Arata]].\n\n===In the Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl manga===\nA Lucario appeared in [[PDP20]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Riley\'s Lucario}}\n{{main|Korrina\'s Lucario}}\nIn the [[Pokémon Adventures]] manga, like the {{pkmn|games}}, one appears under the ownership of [[Riley]]. It first appeared in \'\'[[PS378|Grumpy Gliscor]]\'\'.\n\n[[Korrina]] has a Lucario which she [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolves]] to help when {{adv|X}} and his friends were attacked in [[Santalune City]] who first appeared in \'\'[[PAXY06|The Aegislash Agenda]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure! manga===\n{{main|Maylene\'s Lucario}}\n{{main|Riley\'s Lucario}}\n[[Riley]] has a Lucario, which is his only known Pokémon. He trained it while he was on [[Iron Island]] in \'\'[[DPA10|Serious Training on Iron Island!!]]\'\'.\n\n[[Maylene]] sent out her Lucario to take on one of the {{tc|Galactic Grunt}}s in \'\'[[DPA11|The Legendary Pokémon, Captured]]\'\'.\n\n[[Hareta]]\'s Riolu evolved into Lucario in \'\'[[DPA14|A Novel Test!!]]\'\'.\n\n[[Cynthia]]\'s Lucario made a minor appearance during its Trainer\'s battle with [[Mitsumi]] in \'\'[[DPA23|A New Battle Begins!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\nA Lucario appeared in [[PMDP05]].\n\nA Lucario appeared in [[PMDP29]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Lucario (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n[[File:Pokkén Lucario.png|thumb|x200px|Lucario\'s official artwork for Pokkén Tournament]]\n===[[Pokkén Tournament]]===\nLucario is a playable character for the arcade fighting game. Its moves include {{m|Force Palm}}, {{m|Bone Rush}}, {{m|Extreme Speed}}, and multiple variations of {{m|Aura Sphere}}. Upon entering Burst form, it Mega-Evolves and can use the Burst Attack Aura Blast.\n\n===[[Super Smash Bros.]]===\n{{main|Lucario (Super Smash Bros.)}}\n{{-}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* {{g|Mystery Dungeon: Red Rescue Team and Blue Rescue Team}}: Lucario is seen as the greatest rescue leader of all time, and his adventures have become legendary. While the player never meets Lucario, [[Team A.C.T.|Alakazam]] tells the player that his goal is to become closer to Lucario\'s greatness. Earning 15000 Rescue Points will put the player in the top [[Rank (Mystery Dungeon)|Rescue Rank]]—Lucario Rank—at which point the Lucario Statue will be displayed outside the [[Team Base]].\n* {{g|Ranger: Shadows of Almia}}: Lucario is the guardian of the {{DL|The King of Almia and the Three Princes|Blue Gem}}.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n====Lucario====\n{{Dex/Header|type=Fighting|type2=Steel}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=116|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=It has the ability to sense the [[Aura]]s of all things. It understands human speech.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Pearl|entry=By catching the Aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over {{tt|half a mile|one kilometer}} away.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=It\'s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect Auras. Even foes it could not otherwise see.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{De